SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c03861260
Version: 1

HPSBGN02904 rev.1 - HP SiteScope running SOAP, Remote Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2013-07-29
Last Updated: 2013-07-29

Potential Security Impact: Remote code execution

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with HP SiteScope
running SOAP. The vulnerabilities could be remotely exploited to allow
execution of code.

References: CVE-2013-2367 (SSRT101073, ZDI-CAN-1678)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.

HP SiteScope v11.20 and v11.21 for Windows, Linux and Solaris

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2013-2367    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       10.0
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

The Hewlett-Packard Company thanks Andrea Micalizzi aka rgod for working with
HP's Zero Day Initiative to report CVE-2013-2367 to security-alert@...com.

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following software updates available to resolve the
vulnerabilities.

HP SiteScope v11.22 or subsequent for Windows, Linux and Solaris

The software updates are available from HP Software Support Online at
http://support.openview.hp.com/selfsolve/patches .

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 29 July 2013 Initial release

